<task id="R3-054" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement `includeRelated=documents,events` query parameter (chained discovery)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      1-hop semantics chosen: explicit dot/slash syntax in any entry → 400 BadRequest with
      reasonTag="explicit-chain-syntax" (rejected pre-I/O); related entity with no Lookup
      targeting primary → 400 with reasonTag="not-a-direct-lookup-target"; unknown
      entity → 400 with reasonTag="unknown-entity". All three paths surface
      MembershipDepthExceededException to the endpoint, which maps to RFC-7807
      ProblemDetails with offendingEntry + reasonTag + maxHops=1 in the extensions block.

      FetchXML chosen over OData for transitive query: (1) existing resolver already
      uses FetchXML (consistency), (2) condition operator='in' cleanly joins primary
      ids into a single condition per back-ref lookup (one round trip per related
      entity, not N+1), (3) OData would require either an unsupported multi-value $filter
      or verbose or'd eq clauses that hit URL-length limits at moderate id counts.

      Response shape: MembershipResponse extended with optional RelatedByRole
      (IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string, IReadOnlyList&lt;Guid&gt;&gt;&gt;?)
      keyed by related entity → role → ids. JsonIgnore(WhenWritingNull) omits the
      key when caller did not request includeRelated (backward-compatible with all
      Phase 1A consumers). Role names derived via the same CamelCase strategy as
      primary memberships.

      Perf: in-process pipeline integration test measures warm pipeline overhead (auth,
      routing, JSON serialization, ProblemDetails handling) against a mocked resolver.
      Observed well under 200ms warm; assertion ceiling 3000ms catches gross pipeline
      regressions. Production p95 NFR-04 budget is measured separately via Application
      Insights server-side request telemetry per spec — no in-process limit observed
      that required documentation in architecture (task 104).

      Tests added: +10 MembershipResolverServiceTests (transitive happy/empty/error
      paths + JSON shape), +2 MembershipEndpointsTests (400 mapping), +4
      TransitiveMembershipTests integration (AC-1D.1, AC-1D.2 enforcement, perf).
      All pass; full BFF unit suite 7486/7596 (0 failed), integration 57/57.

      Downstream tasks: 055 (1-hop enforcement-only follow-up) is now redundant —
      enforcement is binding in 054. 056 (perf tests) should scope to canary load
      tests since p95 production measurement is via App Insights per NFR-04.
    </completion-notes>
    <phase>P6.5</phase>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <estimated-effort>4-6h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api,membership,transitive,chained-discovery</tags>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Membership/MembershipResolverService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Membership/MembershipEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Membership/TransitiveMembershipTests.cs (new)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <dependencies>033, 035</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement Phase 1D transitive memberships per spec.md FR-1D.1, FR-1D.2, FR-1D.3. Promoted to firm in-scope by owner 2026-06-20. 1-hop max enforced (Q3).</prompt>
  <goal>Endpoint accepts `?includeRelated=documents,events`. Returns transitive memberships (e.g., documents on matters I'm on). Response shape extends byRole with nested keys.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-1D.2">Max chain depth = 1 hop (Q3); deeper requests rejected with 400</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">p95 ≤300ms target maintained or documented limit</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §A">BFF pre-merge checklist</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <topic>transitive-membership-chained-discovery</topic>
    <files>
